# Requirements

To run this project, you need:

- Python 3.9 or higher
- Internet connection (for scanning live targets)

Python packages used:

- requests
- beautifulsoup4
- colorama

---

# Installation

## 1️⃣ Clone the Repository

git clone https://github.com/Suryadev2004/web-vuln-scanner.git  
cd web-vuln-scanner

---

## 2️⃣ (Optional but Recommended) Create Virtual Environment

Windows:

python -m venv venv  
venv\Scripts\activate

Mac/Linux:

python3 -m venv venv  
source venv/bin/activate

---

## 3️⃣ Install Required Packages

pip install requests beautifulsoup4 colorama

Or if requirements.txt exists:

pip install -r requirements.txt

---

## 4️⃣ Run the Scanner

cd current  
python main.py --url http://example.com

Example:

python main.py --url http://testphp.vulnweb.com

---

# What Happens During a Scan

The scanner will:

- Crawl internal links
- Detect forms
- Perform SQL injection testing
- Perform Boolean blind SQL comparison
- Test for XSS
- Check security headers
- Scan common ports
- Generate a report file

